            {
                "content": "PROCEDURE",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "content": "3.\u00a0On 22 January 2004 the Court declared the application admissible.",
                        "elements": []
                    }
                ],
                "section_name": "procedure"
            },
            {
                "content": "THE FACTS",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "content": "4.\u00a0\u00a0The applicant was born in 1923 and lives in .",
                        "elements": []
                    },
                    {
                        "content": "1.\u00a0\u00a0The principal proceedings",
                        "elements": []
                    },
                    {
                        "content": "2.\u00a0\u00a0The \u201cPinto\u201d proceedings",
                        "elements": []
                    }
                ],
                "section_name": "facts"
            },
            {
                "content": "THE LAW",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "content": "I.\u00a0\u00a0\tTHE OBJECTION OF INADMISSIBILITY RAISED BY THE GOVERNMENT",
                        "elements": []
                    },
                    {
                        "content": "II.\u00a0ALLEGED VIOLATION OF ARTICLE 6 OF THE CONVENTION",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "content": "\u201cIn the determination of his civil rights and obligations ..., everyone is entitled to a\u00a0... hearing within a reasonable time by [a] ... tribunal ...\u201d",
                                "elements": []
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "content": "III.\u00a0APPLICATION OF ARTICLE 41 OF THE CONVENTION",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "content": "25.\u00a0\u00a0Article 41 of the Convention provides:",
                                "elements": []
                            },
                            {
                                "content": "\u201cIf the Court finds that there has been a violation of the Convention or the Protocols thereto, and if the internal law of the High Contracting Party concerned allows only partial reparation to be made, the Court shall, if necessary, afford just satisfaction to the injured party.\u201d",
                                "elements": []
                            },
                            {
                                "content": "A.\u00a0\u00a0Reiteration of the criteria followed by the Court",
                                "elements": [
                                    {
                                        "content": "1.\u00a0\u00a0General criteria",
                                        "elements": []
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "content": "2.\u00a0\u00a0Criteria specific to non-pecuniary damage",
                                        "elements": []
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "content": "B.\u00a0\u00a0Application of the above criteria to the instant case",
                                "elements": [
                                    {
                                        "content": "1.\u00a0\u00a0Non-pecuniary damage",
                                        "elements": []
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "content": "2.\u00a0\u00a0Costs and expenses",
                                        "elements": []
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "content": "3.\u00a0\u00a0Default interest",
                                        "elements": [
                                            {
                                                "content": "35.\u00a0\u00a0The Court considers it appropriate that the default interest should be based on the marginal lending rate of the European Central Bank, to which should be added three percentage points.",
                                                "elements": []
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ],
                "section_name": "law"
            },
            {
                "content": "FOR THESE REASONS, THE COURT, UNANIMOUSLY,",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "content": "1.\u00a0\u00a0Dismisses the Government's preliminary objection;",
                        "elements": []
                    },
                    {
                        "content": "2.\u00a0\u00a0Holds that there has been a violation of Article 6 \u00a7 1 of the Convention;",
                        "elements": []
                    },
                    {
                        "content": "3.\u00a0\u00a0Holds",
                        "elements": []
                    },
                    {
                        "content": "a)\u00a0\u00a0that the respondent State shall pay the applicant, within three months from the date on which the judgment becomes final according to Article 44 \u00a7 2 of the Convention, the following sums:",
                        "elements": []
                    },
                    {
                        "content": "b)\u00a0\u00a0that from the expiry of the above-mentioned three months until settlement simple interest shall be payable on the above amounts at a rate equal to the marginal lending rate of the European Central Bank during the default period plus three percentage points;",
                        "elements": []
                    },
                    {
                        "content": "4.\u00a0\u00a0Dismisses the remainder of the claim for just satisfaction.",
                        "elements": []
                    },
                    {
                        "content": "Done in French, and communicated in writing on\u00a010 November 2004 pursuant to Rule 77 \u00a7\u00a7 2 and 3 of the Rules of Court.",
                        "elements": []
                    }
                ],
                "section_name": "conclusion"
            }
        ]
    },
